citations:
    citation-twoiaf-aerys-joanna:
        source: source-twoiaf
        properties:
            locator: "The World of Ice and Fire — The Targaryen Kings: Aerys II"
            text_from_source: "It has been reliably reported, however, that King Aerys took unwonted liberties with Lady Joanna's person during the bedding ceremony of the feast, something Tywin never forgave. And whilst Tywin and Joanna were at Casterly Rock, the king and his queen were in King's Landing, and all that Aerys would say of Lady Joanna was that it was a great pity that the Lord of Casterly Rock's bride was 'so little to look at.'"
            accessed: "2026-03-10"
        notes: "From TWOIAF's section on Aerys II. Establishes that Aerys had a known fixation on Joanna Lannister. The 'unwonted liberties' at the bedding ceremony of Joanna's wedding to Tywin are cited as evidence by Tyrion Targaryen theorists. However, the bedding occurred at the 263 AC wedding, and Tyrion was born in 273 AC — a decade later."
